Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.10,0:00:07.73,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord2\shad0\fnArial\b1\fs30\pos(291,48)\c&H04376F&\3c&H2F7BAD&\blur1}Beika Bakery
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.87,0:00:07.73,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, darn.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.41,0:00:10.27,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't have it here either.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.90,0:00:11.90,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.04,0:00:23.36,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why he was in such a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.12,0:00:29.00,Location,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(319,292)\shad1\4c&H3A2A1D&\fad(696,806)}10 Minutes Later
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.29,0:00:35.70,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,Someone help!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.70,0:00:38.18,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,Thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.52,0:00:46.31,DCNameCards,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(357,1)\pos(322,314)\c&HFFF1F5&\3c&H904144&}Kume Shosaku (68)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.82,0:00:51.59,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,I just saw someone \Nin a red jacket run that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.59,0:00:52.96,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,That way?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.46,0:00:56.62,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.35,0:01:02.51,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,Someone stole a bag containing \Nthe 300,000 yen I'd withdrawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.51,0:01:05.08,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,I chased after the culprit \Nas quick as I could,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.42,0:01:07.34,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,but I lost sight of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.34,0:01:09.96,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,I ended up here after asking \Npeople if they'd seen them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.96,0:01:12.71,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You called the police, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.71,0:01:15.34,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. I should call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.69,0:01:18.59,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I know. I'll call the others, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.59,0:01:20.85,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord2\shad0\b1\c&H0B101A&\3c&HE5E9E9&}Metropolitan Police Department
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.15,0:01:26.46,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.46,0:01:27.93,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,You got here quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.93,0:01:31.26,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I was in the area gathering \Ninformation when I heard sirens.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.26,0:01:33.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Someone was robbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.06,0:01:34.11,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.75,0:01:37.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mysterious clouds block your field of view!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.49,0:01:39.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Clear them away with deductive \Nreasoning and the sky sparkles!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.22,0:01:40.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The Detective Boys chase \Nafter a purse-snatcher,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.89,0:01:42.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,only to discover a shocking truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.95,0:01:44.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.66,0:01:46.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.59,0:01:49.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.98,0:03:36.98,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(356,1)}The Detective Boys' Pursuit of the Purse-snatcher
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.61,0:03:34.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Detective Boys' Pursuit \Nof the Purse-snatcher!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.74,0:03:46.29,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit who stole the bag \Nfrom Kume Shosaku-san
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.29,0:03:48.99,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,apparently fled into an apartment complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.99,0:03:51.56,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Did they really run in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.56,0:03:54.65,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they ran through it to a side street.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.65,0:03:56.70,DCMain,DELIVERYMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Officer, help!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.82,0:04:01.01,DCMain,DELIVERYMAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's s-someone on the ground over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.97,0:04:06.01,DCNameCards,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(356,390)\pos(344,314)\c&HFFF3FF&\3c&H8B6663&}Samura Koichi (33)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.89,0:04:10.42,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we're almost certain it was murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.33,0:04:12.90,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.90,0:04:16.27,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that's my bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.83,0:04:20.54,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,And that's the red jacket \Nthe culprit was wearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.54,0:04:24.21,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean he's the purse-snatcher?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.21,0:04:26.03,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.03,0:04:28.66,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't have run on that leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.66,0:04:32.54,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,And I think the culprit had longer hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.38,0:04:37.04,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Could you confirm this is yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.29,0:04:43.55,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,T-The envelope containing 300,000 yen \Nand my wallet aren't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.55,0:04:49.31,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean the purse-snatcher \Nwas someone else who murdered that man,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.31,0:04:51.11,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,abandoned their conspicuous red jacket,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.11,0:04:55.02,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,removed the money and wallet \Nfrom the bag, and fled?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.51,0:04:59.93,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Probably, but why did they \Ncome to this apartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.74,0:05:11.99,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord2\shad0\b1\fs27\pos(323,125)\c&H3B279F&\3c&HEDE9E4&\blur2}February {\c&H1D2822&}11th
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.74,0:05:11.99,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord2\shad0\fnTimes New Roman\fs17\pos(319,228)\c&H2E4033&\3c&HF1EBEE&\b1\blur1}Management company coming in AM
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.25,0:05:11.61,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So he had guests coming over today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.51,0:05:16.10,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Samura Koichi, \Nthe resident of this apartment,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.10,0:05:18.63,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,appears to have several \Nprevious extortion offenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.63,0:05:21.19,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,So he was a serial blackmailer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.19,0:05:26.69,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,How is the murder of this scoundrel \Nconnected to the purse-snatching incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.75,0:05:31.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,This is Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.95,0:05:33.33,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,At Haido City?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.84,0:05:35.82,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Understood. I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.93,0:05:42.35,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,A man's body was found nearby \Nat an izakaya in Haido City.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.35,0:05:46.27,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Next to the man's body were \Nan envelope containing 300,000 yen
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.27,0:05:49.87,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and Kume Shosaku's wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.37,0:05:54.37,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean he's the purse-snatcher?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.37,0:05:56.62,DCMain,SIGN LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\bord1.5\shad0\fnTimes New Roman\frz10.66\c&HDAE2F2&\3c&H5F626A&\pos(169,110)}Izakaya Toriko
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.37,0:05:56.62,DCMain,SIGN RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\bord1.5\shad0\fnTimes New Roman\c&HDAE2F2&\3c&H5F626A&\fs18\frz350.6\pos(381,89)}Izakaya & Yakitori Toriko
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.59,0:06:02.38,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Could you confirm this is yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.38,0:06:05.38,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,That's definitely mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.38,0:06:09.02,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,So he really was the purse-snatcher.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.14,0:06:13.00,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,This store is closed today,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.00,0:06:17.02,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,but an employee who came to get \Nsomething they'd forgotten found the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.74,0:06:19.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Togane Katsumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.55,0:06:25.03,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,This man was quite the scoundrel as well \Nand a friend of Samura Koichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.03,0:06:28.34,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}He died after consuming a poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.23,0:06:29.11,DCNameCards,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(405,347)\pos(320,315)\3c&H75656C&}Togane Katsumi (32)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.34,0:06:31.95,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Based on this note he left \Nwith the stolen money,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.41,0:06:35.04,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord2\shad0\fnArial\fs18\c&H969696&\3c&HE8EAE9&\fad(356,1)\pos(282,123)}I killed my friend
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.41,0:06:35.04,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord2\shad0\fnArial\fs18\c&H969696&\3c&HE8EAE9&\fad(356,1)\frz3.601\pos(329,165)}for betraying me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.41,0:06:35.04,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord2\shad0\fnArial\fs18\c&H969696&\3c&HE8EAE9&\fad(356,1)\frz3.601\pos(312,222)}Farewell to this
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.41,0:06:35.04,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord2\shad0\fnArial\fs18\c&H969696&\3c&HE8EAE9&\fad(356,1)\pos(327,278)\frz5.873}cursed life!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.95,0:06:35.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}we can guess what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.70,0:06:39.48,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Togane Katsumi robbed the victim
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.48,0:06:43.54,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,near an apartment complex \Nin Beika City and fled.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.54,0:06:45.71,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He went to his criminal friend \NSamura Koichi's apartment
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.71,0:06:47.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,in hopes that he would harbor him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.01,0:06:50.62,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He became angry when \NSamura rejected his request,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.62,0:06:54.78,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and Togane killed Samura \Nusing a knife at the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.33,0:06:59.69,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He abandoned his bloody jacket,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.69,0:07:04.19,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,removed the envelope and wallet \Nfrom the bag, and came to this izakaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.78,0:07:10.35,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Betrayed by his friend Samura Koichi \Nand having now committed murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.35,0:07:12.32,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,he killed himself here out of desperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.32,0:07:14.62,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.16,0:07:17.45,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get this body autopsied.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.90,0:07:26.21,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for walking me home.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.56,0:07:28.67,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You've been through a lot today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.67,0:07:31.76,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,First you were robbed, \Nand then you saw a corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.76,0:07:34.72,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Your family will be shocked \Nto hear the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.72,0:07:37.70,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I don't have any family.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.72,0:07:43.35,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord2\shad0\fnArial\frz358.9\pos(547,164)\c&H4E615E&\3c&HC2D5DA&}Kume
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.70,0:07:43.35,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,I lived in Tamage City forever until \NI moved here to Beika City five years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.35,0:07:46.88,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,Six months ago, my wife \Npassed away from an illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.03,0:07:52.96,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful on your way home, kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.03,0:07:55.02,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord2\shad0\fnArial\frz358.9\pos(547,164)\c&H4E615E&\3c&HC2D5DA&}Kume
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.01,0:07:58.67,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,So Kume-san is all alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.67,0:08:00.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.09,0:08:03.28,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like there's still \Nsomething bugging you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.80,0:08:09.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why did he decide to kill himself \Nat a closed restaurant
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.54,0:08:11.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,instead of his own home?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.87,0:08:13.01,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.87,0:08:17.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That poorly-written suicide \Nnote seems off to me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.31,0:08:20.73,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he wrote it \Nwith his non-dominant hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.73,0:08:24.19,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,He could've tripped while fleeing \Nand hurt his dominant hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.43,0:08:22.60,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Arms up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.19,0:08:27.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's possible, but the note \Nwasn't so necessary
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.45,0:08:29.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,that he'd need to write one \Nwith his non-dominant hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.92,0:08:32.57,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're not wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.57,0:08:34.03,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.24,0:08:37.64,DCMain,APARTMENT MANAGER,0000,0000,0000,,A murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.11,0:08:41.95,DCMain,APARTMENT MANAGER,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why there are \Nso many police cars around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.70,0:08:50.59,DCMain,APARTMENT MANAGER,0000,0000,0000,,I might have to reduce the rent \Non Building B Room 301 because of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.59,0:08:52.48,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Are you from the management company?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.48,0:08:54.72,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you manage this apartment complex?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.49,0:08:57.47,DCMain,APARTMENT MANAGER,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.47,0:09:00.89,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,You're lucky you didn't get involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.89,0:09:01.80,DCMain,APARTMENT MANAGER,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.80,0:09:07.98,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You were supposed to visit Samura-san \Nin Building B Room 301, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.98,0:09:11.65,DCMain,APARTMENT MANAGER,0000,0000,0000,,What? No, I wasn't planning on doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.65,0:09:12.70,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.70,0:09:14.25,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.25,0:09:15.49,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.49,0:09:17.49,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord2\shad0\fnTimes New Roman\fs17\pos(319,228)\c&H788567&\3c&HF1EBEE&\b1\blur1\fad(356,1)}Management company coming in AM
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.49,0:09:23.00,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Someone pretended to be from the management \Ncompany and contacted Samura-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.54,0:09:25.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Probably so he wouldn't leave his apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.50,0:09:30.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And Samura Koichi-san was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.00,0:09:31.88,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.88,0:09:35.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, this case didn't just happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.36,0:09:37.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was a premeditated murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.01,0:09:42.51,DCMain,SIGN RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord2\shad0\fnTimes New Roman\fs18\frz5.711\c&HA8C1BF&\3c&H92653C&\move(508,206,508,97)}Eliminate fraud!\NCrackdown in effect
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.01,0:09:42.51,DCMain,SIGN LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord2\shad0\fnTimes New Roman\fs18\frz5.711\c&HAF99CB&\3c&HE1E5D3&\b1\move(250,215,250,103)}Prevent Traffic \NAccidents
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.01,0:09:42.51,DCMain,SIGN BOTTOM,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord2\shad1\fnTimes New Roman\c&H2E7979&\3c&H4D3F2F&\4c&H32402D&\frz8.121\move(302,280,302,169)}MPD Beika Police Station
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.37,0:09:42.51,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see. I suppose that's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.85,0:09:44.24,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.82,0:09:49.89,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,This is Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.37,0:09:53.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.04,0:09:54.22,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.65,0:09:56.65,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.10,0:09:58.91,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,According to the autopsy,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.91,0:10:05.07,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Togane's time of death was \Nan hour earlier than Samura's.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.07,0:10:08.74,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,They died in the opposite order?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.74,0:10:12.46,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Then Togane didn't kill Samura.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.83,0:10:16.48,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,So who killed Samura-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.48,0:10:18.81,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That question needs answering, too, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.66,0:10:24.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Then what about \Nthat note Togane-san wrote?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.86,0:10:29.98,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It said he was killing himself \Nbecause he killed Samura.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.05,0:10:33.86,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.90,0:10:38.43,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Togane didn't commit suicide. He was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.35,0:10:40.82,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.82,0:10:43.22,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Samura's death was a premeditated murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.22,0:10:46.29,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Togane's death was a murder \Nmade to look like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.29,0:10:48.19,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Both deaths need to be re-investigated.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.19,0:10:48.83,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.59,0:10:56.21,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Made to look like a suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.71,0:11:00.30,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That would explain what was bugging me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.23,0:11:12.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit must've needed that suicide note
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.98,0:11:16.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,to make the murder look like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.14,0:11:20.11,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit deliberately wrote \Nwith terrible handwriting
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.11,0:11:21.61,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,to disguise their handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.61,0:11:24.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit wanted the body to be discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.26,0:11:27.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so the investigation would \Nconclude it was a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.59,0:11:31.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But if it was found too soon, the precise \Ntime of death would be determined,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.18,0:11:33.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,ruining the idea that \NTogane-san killed himself
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.65,0:11:35.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,because he murdered Samura-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.15,0:11:39.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's why they chose \Nto kill him at that izakaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.13,0:11:43.14,DCMain,SIGN LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\bord1.5\shad0\fnTimes New Roman\frz10.66\c&HDAE2F2&\3c&H5F626A&\move(83,97,102,103,26,3989)}Izakaya Toriko
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.13,0:11:43.14,DCMain,SIGN RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\bord1.5\shad0\fnTimes New Roman\c&HDAE2F2&\3c&H5F626A&\fs18\frz350.6\move(413,75,402,82,26,3989)}Izakaya & Yakitori Toriko
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.67,0:11:43.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Since the store was closed today, \Nthe body would be found tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.51,0:11:46.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They were supposed to \Nhave a whole extra day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.38,0:11:47.38,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.79,0:11:50.88,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,But because an employee came \Nto get something they'd forgotten,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.88,0:11:55.27,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,things didn't go as planned, \Nand Togane-san's body was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.27,0:11:56.59,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.59,0:11:58.65,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.65,0:12:03.53,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Then the person wearing \Nthe red jacket that I saw
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.53,0:12:06.91,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,wasn't actually that Togane man.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.91,0:12:08.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.12,0:12:12.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,By the time you saw them, \Nhe was probably already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.55,0:12:17.79,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,If we review the culprit's actions, \Nwe may find a clue leading to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.12,0:12:22.86,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,First the culprit poisoned \NTogane-san at the izakaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.86,0:12:26.05,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Then they stole the bag from Kume-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.05,0:12:29.18,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,They visited Samura-san pretending to be \Nfrom the management company
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.18,0:12:30.61,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,and killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.43,0:12:34.85,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Then they took the money and wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.85,0:12:38.61,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,And left them next to Togane-san's \Nbody alongside the suicide note.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.61,0:12:40.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What we don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.30,0:12:45.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,is why the culprit killed Togane \NKatsumi-san before Samura Koichi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.99,0:12:49.00,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Even though their times of death \Nwould create an inconsistency.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.00,0:12:51.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There must've been some \Nreason he needed to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.85,0:13:08.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Was there a related incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.14,0:13:11.49,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You've got a keen eye, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.49,0:13:14.59,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It's an extortion incident \Nrelated to Samura Koichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.59,0:13:19.47,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,A young woman killed herself because \Nshe was being blackmailed by Samura.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.47,0:13:21.53,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm re-investigating this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.53,0:13:24.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Good luck with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.53,0:13:27.91,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.52,0:13:38.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Setoguchi Asako-san \Nwas the victim in that case.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.79,0:13:41.80,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\frz1.145\bord2\shad0\fs32\pos(307,80)\c&H766F63&\3c&HF3F1F0&}Victim Name: Setoguchi Asako (24)
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.79,0:13:41.80,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord2\shad0\fs24\c&H766F63&\3c&HF3F1F0&\frz1.745\pos(391,189)}Address: Tamage City North Ward 1073-151
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.28,0:13:41.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It happened five years ago in Tamage City.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.80,0:13:43.34,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.34,0:13:46.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It's where Kume-san used to live,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.87,0:13:49.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and he moved away five years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.89,0:13:53.21,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,It might be a coincidence, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.21,0:13:55.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's involved in the case, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.19,0:13:59.19,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord2\shad0\pos(269,88)\frz354.1\fs28\c&HCDD4D8&\3c&H45514E&}Setoguchi
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.53,0:13:59.19,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.19,0:14:01.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We're looking for the home of Kume-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.40,0:14:03.28,DCNameCards,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(509,314)\3c&HA93C4F&\fad(355,313)}Setoguchi Sakie
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.81,0:14:06.08,DCMain,SAKIE,0000,0000,0000,,What? He moved away a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.51,0:14:08.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So he did live around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.86,0:14:11.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You must've been close \Nsince you were neighbors.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.24,0:14:15.95,DCMain,SAKIE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but I'm in \Nthe middle of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.74,0:14:21.03,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,She avoided talking about Kume-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.03,0:14:25.10,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Kume-san and her daughter's \Ntragedy might be related.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.10,0:14:27.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll just have to ask the locals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.31,0:14:29.26,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,What? We're walking more?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.30,0:14:33.10,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,This is exhausting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.07,0:14:37.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.34,0:14:40.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.20,0:14:41.52,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.34,0:14:43.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,How'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.03,0:14:47.28,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,The daughter was engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.28,0:14:49.32,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't learn anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.88,0:14:53.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to believe they're unrelated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.21,0:14:58.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kume-san and his wife moved away \Nimmediately after the daughter's suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.85,0:15:00.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Suddenly, as though fleeing from something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.46,0:15:04.82,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,But what does that have \Nto do with this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.82,0:15:09.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know the motive yet, but I have \Na rough idea of what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.76,0:15:16.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But why did the culprit kill Togane \NKatsumi-san before Samura Koichi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.35,0:15:18.52,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.92,0:15:22.40,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You went all the way to Tamage City \Nto investigate Kume-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.40,0:15:25.07,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You think he did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.07,0:15:27.48,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,You think he was working with the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.48,0:15:30.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than explaining it to you, \Nthere's something I want to check.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.07,0:15:33.66,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.66,0:15:37.29,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord2\shad0\b1\fs16\frz342.6\pos(229,95)\c&H44423E&\3c&HC7C4BF&\blur5}Building B
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.06,0:15:37.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Where the culprit went \Nafter killing Samura-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.29,0:15:39.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit entered Building B from \Nthe location where Ayumi-chan saw them
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.70,0:15:42.67,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\b1\bord2\shad0\pos(300,70)\c&H000000&\3c&HF0F1F1&\fad(447,1)}Building A
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.70,0:15:42.67,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\b1\bord2\shad0\c&H000000&\3c&HF0F1F1&\fad(447,1)\pos(300,228)}Building B
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.70,0:15:42.67,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\b1\bord2\shad0\c&H000000&\3c&HF0F1F1&\fad(447,1)\fs14\pos(564,153)}Sidewalk
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.70,0:15:42.67,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\b1\bord2\shad0\c&H000000&\3c&HC6C6C6&\fad(447,1)\fs18\pos(606,221)}Main\NStreet
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.70,0:15:42.67,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\b1\bord2\shad0\c&H000000&\3c&HC6C6C6&\fad(447,1)\fs16\pos(22,150)}Side \NStreet
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.85,0:15:42.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and then headed to the exit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.67,0:15:46.54,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord2\shad0\b1\fs16\c&H44423E&\3c&HC7C4BF&\blur5\frz346\pos(321,103)}Building B
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.67,0:15:46.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They left Building B, entered \Nthe side street from here,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.54,0:15:48.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and then headed towards Haido City.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.05,0:15:49.99,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\b1\bord2\shad0\c&H000000&\3c&HF0F1F1&\pos(550,109)\fad(1,1436)}Building B
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.05,0:15:50.55,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\b1\bord2\shad0\c&H000000&\3c&HC6C6C6&\fs24\pos(37,194)\fad(1,560)}Side \NStreet
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.45,0:15:50.55,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\b1\bord2\shad0\c&H000000&\3c&HF0F1F1&\fad(707,1)\pos(547,182)}Building A
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.44,0:16:05.94,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you looking for in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.94,0:16:08.82,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! The floor looks like \Nit's going to fall through.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.82,0:16:09.94,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.70,0:16:14.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I thought they might've hidden \Nsomething here on the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.43,0:16:15.78,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hidden what?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.33,0:16:18.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A yard...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.17,0:16:22.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A fresh mound?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.99,0:16:27.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.87,0:16:31.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They used this to bury it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.63,0:16:33.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.02,0:16:41.79,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit's jacket?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.79,0:16:45.27,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,And this is Kume-san's bag, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.27,0:16:49.82,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,But the police currently have those \Nin their possession as evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.41,0:16:53.89,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Why is there another set of those here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.89,0:16:56.53,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What's that shaggy thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.53,0:16:58.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is this it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.03,0:17:01.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like a long-haired wig.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.06,0:17:04.73,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a mask and sunglasses, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.73,0:17:07.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, they're probably buried here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.33,0:17:12.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Call Detective Takagi right away \Nand explain the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.23,0:17:13.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I've got somewhere to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.64,0:17:14.55,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.55,0:17:16.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.97,0:17:19.72,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\bord2\shad0\fnArial\frz358.9\pos(547,164)\c&H4E615E&\3c&H96D1D7&}Kume
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.11,0:17:23.60,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,What is it that you figured out?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.60,0:17:29.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit had to kill Togane-san \Nbefore Samura-san, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.41,0:17:33.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If they waited until after they \Nwere robbed and called the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.14,0:17:37.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,they'd be stuck with the police \Nand wouldn't be able to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.99,0:17:43.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They'd have to explain \Nhow they were robbed, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.23,0:17:46.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and once the bag was found, \Nthey'd be asked to confirm it was theirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.42,0:17:50.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Pretending to be a victim is hard, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.29,0:17:54.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There never was any robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.81,0:17:58.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I went to Tamage City, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.26,0:18:03.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Having decided to kill the two of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.51,0:18:07.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,you took Togane Katsumi-san \Nto that restaurant
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.67,0:18:09.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so the body would be discovered the next day
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.45,0:18:13.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,by saying something to lure him there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.71,0:18:17.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then you poisoned him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.26,0:18:26.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You wedged an envelope containing \N300,000 yen, your wallet,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.50,0:18:30.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and a suicide note beneath \Nthe body and left the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.63,0:18:33.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then you pretended to be \Nwith the management company
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.05,0:18:35.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and killed Samura Koichi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.57,0:18:39.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You left a bag and jacket there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.23,0:18:44.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then you donned a second \Nmatching jumper, wig, and mask
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.22,0:18:48.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and carried a second bag to disguise \Nyourself as a purse-snatcher.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.38,0:18:51.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You ran into the apartment complex \Nas though fleeing a robbery,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.09,0:18:54.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,ran through the complex \Nand onto the side street,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.98,0:18:58.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and buried the things you'd used \Nat an abandoned house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.24,0:19:01.68,DCFlashback,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,Thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.68,0:19:03.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then you showed up as a robbery victim
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.70,0:19:09.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,chasing after a thief and \Nre-entered the apartment complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.05,0:19:13.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, you played two roles.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.15,0:19:15.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,By acting as both the culprit and victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.34,0:19:18.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,you convinced the police \Nthat you'd been robbed
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.25,0:19:20.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and made it seem as though \NTogane Katsumi-san was the thief
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.60,0:19:24.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and killed himself after killing \Nhis friend Samura Koichi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.20,0:19:26.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That was your plan, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.37,0:19:32.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Playing two roles requires a tight schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.99,0:19:37.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You prepared a second jacket \Nand bag to leave behind
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.34,0:19:42.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and killed Samura-san before you ran into \Nthe apartment complex as the culprit, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.14,0:19:47.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But I still don't know your motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.79,0:19:51.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably related to the incident \Nwith Setoguchi Asako-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.62,0:19:53.12,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,Five years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.84,0:19:58.63,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,my wife and I saw Asako-chan \Narguing with a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.84,0:20:02.72,DCNameCards,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(358,353)\pos(463,316)}Setoguchi Asako (24)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.24,0:20:02.03,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}My wife was concerned,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.03,0:20:05.62,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}but I figured it was just an argument \Nbetween a married couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.62,0:20:08.94,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,I calmed her down, and we walked away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.83,0:20:13.69,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,Several days later, \NAsako-chan killed herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.53,0:20:18.53,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,When I heard from her parents \Nthat she was being blackmailed,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.53,0:20:20.63,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,I regretted my actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.63,0:20:23.94,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,If I'd noticed then, she wouldn't have died.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.85,0:20:28.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You left Tamage City because you \Ncouldn't bear to stay any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.65,0:20:34.17,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,The other day, I saw \Nthat man—Samura Koichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.57,0:20:42.33,DCFlashback,SAMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, the girl I snared \Nthe other day at the club is rich...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.33,0:20:47.16,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,He was plotting something evil with Togane \NKatsumi, who seemed to be his friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.81,0:20:50.66,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,They were planning how to take advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.66,0:20:53.29,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,of the young woman who was their next target.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.29,0:20:59.32,DCMain,KUME,0000,0000,0000,,I thought more victims would appear \Nif they were allowed to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.32,0:21:02.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But you still shouldn't have killed them!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.86,0:21:15.96,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We've collected the evidence buried \Nat the abandoned house.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.08,0:21:24.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kume-san was about to turn himself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.18,0:22:59.91,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. Ayumi-chan, what \Nwere you doing here this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.91,0:23:02.06,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I heard they sold them around here,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.06,0:23:05.04,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,so I wanted to find them \Nand let Genta-kun know
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.04,0:23:06.09,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,that I'd found the eel bowl buns.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.09,0:23:06.93,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.93,0:23:09.33,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Eel bowls baked into bread?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.33,0:23:11.45,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Eel bowl buns?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.45,0:23:15.03,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Where are the eel bowl buns?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.93,0:23:20.42,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,He sure has a weakness for eel bowls.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.75,0:23:23.17,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,But eel bowl buns...?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.08,0:23:29.42,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.13,0:23:32.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The eel sauce would seep into the bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.77,0:23:35.79,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Does this food actually exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.79,0:23:38.06,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,It might actually be pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.95,0:23:40.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The bread seems kind of unnecessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.06,0:23:42.06,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.50,0:23:47.44,DCMain,SUIT,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.81,0:23:50.21,DCMain,SUIT,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Mori, Ran-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.21,0:23:54.20,DCMain,SUIT,0000,0000,0000,,and Edogawa Conan-kun, the little detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.67,0:23:59.20,DCMain,SUIT,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like your help with the boiled fugu pot.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.67,0:24:02.96,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,The pot was stolen the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.34,0:24:08.43,DCMain,SIDEBURNS,0000,0000,0000,,Please find our family treasure \Nand bring it back to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "The Boiled Fugu \NMystery Tour Showdown, Mojiko & Kura Part!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,43)}The Boiled Fugu Mystery Tour Showdown \N(Mojiko & Kura Part)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.91,Hint,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Kanmon Straits
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.41,0:24:32.55,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.55,0:24:34.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The Kanmon Straits!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.91,0:24:37.29,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Wh-Where are you, eel bowl buns?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.91,0:24:40.10,Don'tMiss,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.29,0:24:39.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Next week we're having boiled fugu.
